 Kode Vortex – EdTech, Training & Internship Platform



 1. Project Overview

Project Name: Kode Vortex – Learning, Training & Internship Platform
Client Type: EdTech + Software Services Company
Designer Role: UI/UX Designer (UX Research, Information Architecture, UI Design)
Platform: Responsive Website (Desktop, Tablet, Mobile)

 Objective

To design a comprehensive and engaging digital platform that promotes Kode Vortex’s training programs, internships, and software services while guiding students and professionals toward the right career path.



 2. Problem Statement

Learners and early professionals often face:

. Confusion about career paths
. Lack of industry-aligned training
. Difficulty finding meaningful internships
. Low trust in training institutes

Design Goal: Create a trustworthy, student-centric platform that clearly communicates offerings, builds credibility, and converts visitors into applicants, learners, and clients.



 3. Target Users & Personas

 Primary Users

1. College Students – Seeking internships & training
2. Fresh Graduates – Career-focused upskilling
3. Working Professionals – Skill enhancement
4. Institutions & Corporates – Training & software services

 User Needs

. Clear course & internship details
. Career guidance
. Easy application process
. Proof of credibility
. Simple contact & support



 4. User Journey

1. Landing on Homepage
   ↓
2. Exploring Trainings / Internships / Services
   ↓
3. Understanding Benefits & Differentiators
   ↓
4. Reviewing Courses & Career Paths
   ↓
5. Applying / Contacting / Downloading Brochure



 5. Information Architecture

 Primary Navigation

. Home
. About Us
. Trainings
. Internship
. Services
. Contact Us
. Login / Sign Up

 Secondary Navigation

. Corporate Training
. College Programs
. Software Services



 6. Design System

 Color Palette

. Primary: Dark Blue / Black (Professional & Tech-driven)
. Accent: Highlight colors for CTAs
. Neutral: White & Grey for readability

 Typography

. Headings: Bold, modern sans-serif
. Body Text: Clean, readable sans-serif
. CTAs: High-contrast emphasis

 UI Principles

. Career-focused storytelling
. Clear visual hierarchy
. Conversion-oriented layouts
. Consistent branding



 7. Page-wise UX & UI Breakdown

 7.1 Homepage

Purpose: Introduce brand & value proposition

Key Sections:

. Hero section (Career & learning focus)
. Trainings & internships overview
. What makes us different
. Success stories
. Associated institutions
. Primary CTAs

UX Decisions:

. Aspirational messaging
. Immediate career value communication
. Multiple conversion entry points



 7.2 Trainings Page

Content:

. Available courses (Python, ML, MERN, Cybersecurity)
. Program features
. Placement preparation details

UX Strategy:

. Card-based course display
. Clear feature comparison
. Premium vs regular training clarity



 7.3 Internship Page

Purpose: Convert visitors into applicants

Key Elements:

. Internship benefits
. Role-based internship cards (UI/UX, Web Dev)
. Application CTA & contact details

UX Rationale:

. Clear value over traditional internships
. Simple apply flow
. Role clarity



 7.4 Courses & Career Path Pages

Purpose: Help users choose the right path

UX Decisions:

. Career-to-skill mapping
. Step-by-step learning explanation
. Industry relevance focus



 7.5 About Us Page

Sections:

. Mission & vision
. What makes us different
. Team overview

UX Goal:

. Build trust
. Humanize the brand



 7.6 Contact & Lead Capture

Forms:

. Contact form
. Training inquiry
. Internship application

UX Strategy:

. Minimal required fields
. Clear CTAs
. Easy accessibility



 8. Accessibility & Usability Considerations

. Mobile-first design
. Clear CTA contrast
. Readable typography
. Simple language



 9. Conversion Strategy

. Repeated CTAs (Apply, Start Journey, Download Brochure)
. Career-focused messaging
. Trust signals (Success stories, institutions)
. Simple application process



 10. Tools Used

. Design: Figma
. Wireframing: Low & mid-fidelity wireframes
. UX Research: EdTech & internship platform analysis



 11. Future Enhancements

. Student dashboard
. Progress tracking
. AI-based career guidance
. Community & mentorship features



 12. Conclusion

This UI/UX design positions Kode Vortex as a career-first EdTech platform. By combining structured learning paths, real-world internships, and strong conversion design, the platform effectively bridges the gap between education and industry.



Designed by: Sanskrati Agrawal
Role: UI/UX Designer
